      • getFileElement

        public abstract <T extends DomElement> DomFileElement<T> getFileElement(XmlFile file,
                                                                        java.lang.Class<T> domClass)
        Parameters:
        file - XML file
        domClass - desired DOM element class
        Returns:
        New or cached DOM file element for the given file. All registered DomFileDescriptions are asked if they are responsible for the file DomFileDescription.isMyFile(XmlFile, Module). If there is a DomFileDescription that is responsible for the file, but its DomFileDescription.getRootElementClass() result is incompatible with domClass parameter, null is returned

      • createStableValue

        public abstract <T extends DomElement> T createStableValue(Factory<? extends T> provider)
        Creates DOM element of needed type, that is wrapper around real DOM element. Once the wrapped element becomes invalid, a new value is requested from provider parameter, so there's a possibility to restore the functionality. The resulting element will also implement StableElement interface.
        Parameters:
        provider - provides values to be wrapped
        Returns:
        stable DOM element

        @Deprecated
public abstract void registerFileDescription(DomFileDescription<?> description)
        Deprecated. Make your file description an extension (see DomFileDescription.EP_NAME)
        Registers a new DomFileDescription within the manager. The description parameter describes some DOM parameters and restrictions to the particular XML files, that need DOM support. Should be called on ProjectComponent loading.
        Parameters:
        description - The description in question
